name: Air Terjun Yeh Labuh Waterfall
address: Unnamed Road, GGPM+G99, Selumbung, Manggis, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80871, Indonesia
review 1: Small waterfall that's worth a look if you're in the area. Free to enter but there's a donation box at the entrance to help maintain the path.
review 2: Need a light trekking to get to the waterfalls, the first waterfall is OK but to get to the upper waterfall you need to climb the rock with a rope, very adventurous and be careful dont get fall!
review 3: Amazing place with NOBODY. Do Not recommend so we can keep it genuine eheh
review 4: Beautiful waterfall and no one else there so we had it to ourselves. The walk from the road isn’t too far and it wasn’t difficult. Would definitely recommend.
review 5: Simple waterfall that is not easy to see because of many rocks on the way. No pathway last 20-30 meters.
